result.name: 雲南人家風味餐廳

reviews.text:
I always like to try novel items on menus, which would lead to not-so-good dining experience sometimes. But this time, luck was on my side.

This Soy Bean Curd noodles is a signature item on the menu of 雲南人家風味餐廳. Yes, I am with you, it might seem odd to have sweet bean curd to go with your savory noodles, but first mouthful of it would despite your thinking.

The soy bean curd didn’t taste sweet actually, it’s more like plain, soft and silky soy bean curd, which went so well with the noodles, together with the flavored minced meat.

I topped up my noodles with numbing spicy chicken, which was definitely a very great choice I would say.

One tip for eating this noodles - make sure you mix the sauce, minced meat and the noodles thoroughly before you dig in. First mouthful I had tasted really strong, as I didn’t quite mix everything well…
I've ordered soy bean dessert with rice noodle(豆花米線) with transitional Yuen Nan rose drink, loved it so much. Reasonable price. Authentic taste. Definitely will visit again.
I was new to hong kong and wanted to enjoy dimpsums. My taxi fellow took me here and the experience was awesome. Very good service and helpful. None understand english though.
Ordered tofu pudding base, nice one, very soft and smooth.

The quality is slightly better than average Yuannan noodle joints found in Hong Kong but I have no standing to judge the authenticity of its Yuannan's flavour. The typical portion of its noodle may be kinda small for an average man.

—

豆花同米線一樣滑嘟嘟
友人嫌米線太腍

唔小心食中辣椒會好嗆喉
